MEDIA personality Kuli Roberts is being laid to rest today. The funeral service is held at an unknown venue and is only open to her family and friends. However, it is being streamed online. Kuli died on Wednesday, 9 February aged (49). A memorial service was held for the former The Queen actor on Wednesday, 16 February at Birchwood Hotel in Boksburg, Ekurhuleni. Her family and friends took the stage to talk about how loving, kind, warm and loud she was. In attendance were people like Refilwe Modiselle, Skhumba Hlophe, UDM leader Bantu Holomisa, Dr Bishop Jessica Mbangeni, Tumi Masemola, Zola Hashatsi, Nambitha Ben-Mazwi, Penny Lebyane and DJ Sbu. ALSO READ : KULI ROBERTS REMEMBERED! The programme of the day was directed by her former Trending SA co-hosts Shaka Sisulu and Nina Hastie. Her sister Hlubi Mboya spoke on behalf of the family and thanked people for loving Kuli. “She was complex, beautiful, difficult, loving, kind, crazy and fantastic but she was so gentle. Let’s just let her go because she needs to rest,” she said. Watch the funeral service below. 